article.headline: Central Florida 106, Campbell 56
article.story: ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Dexter Lyons poured in a career-high 33 points and Central Florida hit a school-record 16 three-pointers in overwhelming Campbell 106-56 on Saturday night. Lyons scored 20 points in the first half and UCF (22-5, 17-3 Atlantic Sun) led by 37 points at halftime. Lyons hit five 3-pointers in the game as he surpassed his previous career high of 28 points set Thursday against Gardner-Webb. Diego Aguiar led Campbell (3-24, 3-17) with nine points. The 3-point barrage for UCF was one better than its previous best of 15, set against Campbell in February of 2000. Robert Ross came off the bench to score a career-high 19 points for UCF. Josh Bodden added 13 points. UCF hit its first six shots from the floor and led 18-2 in the game's first four minutes. The Golden Knights hit 11-of-19 three-pointers in the first half. The last time UCF scored 100 or more points was Dec. 13, 2001, vs. Chicago State. UCF's previous highest point total this season was 92 against Puerto Rico-Mayaguez. UCF will carry the No. 2 seed into next week's A-Sun Tournament in Nashville.
